An Act amending the statute of limitations regarding criminal prosecutions for the crimes of
sexual assault and rape of a child.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 63 of chapter 277 of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting at the end
2 thereof the following new paragraph:-
3 Notwithstanding any other provision of this section, an indictment or complaint alleging
4 an offense of indecent assault and battery, or an offense of rape, may be found and filed at any
5 time after the commission of such offense, provided that the victim was under the age of 18
6 when the offense was committed.
